  /**
   * Force Safari on iOS 11 to redraw some elements on the DOM that were not being drawn on screen.
   * @see https://davidwalsh.name/translate3d
   *
   * Note: I was shocked to find that `will-change: transform;` did _not_ work here.

				// Don't run resizer if it's in a programming list webview

					setTimeout(function () {
						var container = document.querySelector('.covid-tracker-wrapper .dashboard');
						var windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
						function resize() {
							var height = container.offsetHeight;
							window.NYTG.enqueue(JSON.stringify({ id: 0, type: 'resize', options: { height: height } }));
						}
						window.addEventListener('resize', function () {
							if (window.innerWidth != windowWidth) {
								windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
								resize();
